oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Shame Shame Shame - Sleepy LaBeef performance; Ain't Got No Home - Sleepy LaBeef performance
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance of Shame Shame Shame, written by Reuben Fisher and Kenyon Hopkins, published by Warner Bros Inc., and performed by Sleepy LaBeef. Performance of Ain't Got No Home, written by Clarence Henry, published by ARC Music, produced by Don Law and Frank Jones, recorded on September 1, 1965 at Columbia Recording Studio in Nashville, TN, and performed by Sleepy LaBeef (vocals), Grady Martin (guitar), Harold Bradley (guitar), James Wilkerson (guitar), Bob Moore (bass), Kenneth Buttrey (drums), Bill Pursell (piano), Charlie McCoy (harmonica), and Boots Randolph (saxophone).
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Sleepy LaBeef
